{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4404284948","title":"Senior Business Analyst","company":"HOIST","location":"Toronto","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://fr.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-business-analyst-at-hoist-4404284948?position=16&pageNum=0&refId=PThZqpK24CgEfFC2RxTXvA%3D%3D&trackingId=lj0UD5rBz%2B1D6PYDdnURQw%3D%3D","description":"HOIST is expanding its presence in France, and we’re looking for a Senior Business Analyst (Finance) to play a pivotal role in that growth. This is a remote position based in France, working with clients and colleagues in France and across our global business.\nAt a glanceLocation / working model: France (remote), with travel to client sites as requiredLanguages: Fluent French + professional English. Applications welcome in English or French; interviews predominantly in English.Focus: Senior Finance BA on ERP/digital transformation (ideally IFS), owning workstreams and mentoring/coaching\nWho we areWe are an IFS integrator, offering comprehensive ERP implementation projects to unparalleled support services. As a business strategic partner, we collaborate with clients across focused industries, transcending boundaries to deliver transformative service. With a global team of 200+ members, our strength is in our shared expertise. Our community comprises former IFS customers who’ve encountered challenges firsthand and dedicated IFS experts who bring specialised knowledge to the table. Together, we reshape businesses through exceptional service.\nRole summaryFrance is a strategic growth market for HOIST. As Senior Business Analyst (Finance), you’ll lead discovery and requirements on ERP/digital transformation engagements, partnering with Finance stakeholders and HOIST delivery teams to shape workable solutions, manage scope, and support adoption.\nKey ResponsibilitiesLead workshops to elicit, analyse and validate Finance requirements; produce clear documentation (process maps, specs/user stories, acceptance criteria) with traceability.Map current/future processes, assess impacts (incl. controls), perform gap analysis and recommend pragmatic improvements.Partner with architects and delivery teams to translate needs into workable designs; support decisions and manage trade-offs.Own Finance workstreams end-to-end (scope, dependencies, risks/issues) and support data/integration discussions where Finance is impacted.Support testing/UAT and adoption (training, comms); mentor junior colleagues and contribute to internal best practice as we grow in France.\nMust-have requirements5+ years as a Business Analyst and/or ERP Functional Consultant with strong Finance expertise.ERP implementation/transformation experience across the lifecycle (requirements through to testing and adoption).Strong workshop facilitation and stakeholder management; confident with senior client contacts.Fluent French and professional English (written/spoken).Adaptable and hands-on — willing to build ways of working as the France region scales.Based in France with right to work; willing to travel to client sites as required.\nNice to haveExperience delivering within IFS Cloud / IFS ERP (Finance); IFS certification is a plus.Experience with other major ERP platforms (SAP, Oracle, Microsoft Dynamics) within Finance.Exposure to system integration, data migration, and reporting/analytics (including defining KPIs and Finance reporting requirements).Experience in one or more of the following industries: Manufacturing; Energy & Utilities; Service Sector; Construction & Engineering; Shipping & Harbour Services; Aviation & Defense.Experience coaching/mentoring colleagues and contributing to internal ways of working and reusable assets.\nWhy HOIST?If you’re driven by the desire to make a tangible impact, HOIST is your destination. Join a client-driven team delivering transformative business excellence, grounded in our Core Values: Customer Focus, Excellence through Expertise, Care for our People and Innovation. You’ll work in a collaborative environment with flexibility, autonomy, and the backing of a global community of experts.\nHow to applyPlease apply via the job posting, or contact the hiring team for an initial conversation. We welcome applications in English or French; please note the interview process will be predominantly conducted in English.\nWe will not be accepting applications from candidates based outside of France. We are not accepting engagement through recruitment agencies.\n\nHOIST accélère son développement en France et recrute un(e) Senior Business Analyst – Finance pour jouer un rôle clé dans cette dynamique. Ce poste est en télétravail, basé en France, avec des interactions régulières auprès de clients et de collègues en France et au sein de notre organisation internationale.\nEn brefLocalisation / mode de travail : France (télétravail), avec des déplacements chez les clients selon les besoinsLangues : Français courant + anglais professionnel. Candidatures acceptées en français ou en anglais ; entretiens majoritairement en anglais.Focus : Rôle senior Finance sur des projets ERP / transformation digitale (idéalement IFS), leader du champ de travail et du mentorat / coaching\nQui sommes-nous ?HOIST est un intégrateur IFS : nous accompagnons nos clients sur des projets d’implémentation ERP de bout en bout, ainsi que sur des services de support reconnus. Partenaire stratégique, nous intervenons dans des secteurs ciblés et aidons les organisations à réussir leur transformation, au-delà des frontières. Notre équipe internationale compte plus de 200 collaborateurs. Notre force : une expertise issue à la fois d’anciens clients IFS (qui connaissent les enjeux « terrain ») et d’experts IFS dédiés. Ensemble, nous mettons l’excellence du service au cœur de chaque mission.\nRésumé du posteLa France est un marché stratégique pour la croissance de HOIST. En tant que Senior Business Analyst – Finance, vous prendrez en charge le cadrage et la formalisation des besoins sur des projets ERP / transformation digitale. En lien étroit avec les équipes Finance côté client et les équipes HOIST, vous contribuerez à concevoir des solutions concrètes, à sécuriser le périmètre, et à faciliter l’adhésion au changement.\nResponsabilités principalesAnimer des ateliers pour recueillir, analyser et valider les besoins Finance ; produire une documentation structurée (cartographies de processus, spécifications / user stories, critères d’acceptation) tout en assurant la traçabilité.Cartographier les processus existants et cibles, évaluer les impacts (y compris contrôle interne), réaliser les analyses d’écarts et proposer des améliorations pragmatiques.Travailler main dans la main avec les architectes et les équipes projet pour transformer les besoins en solutions réalistes ; faciliter les arbitrages et les décisions.Piloter le champ de travail de Finance de bout en bout (périmètre, dépendances, risques/sujets) et contribuer aux échanges data / intégration dès lors que la Finance est impactée.Accompagner les phases de tests/UAT et l’adoption (formation, communication) ; soutenir la montée en compétences de profils juniors et contribuer au développement de nos bonnes pratiques en France.Exigences indispensables5+ ans d’expérience en tant que Business Analyst et/ou consultant(e) fonctionnel(le) ERP, avec une expertise Finance solide.Expérience sur des projets ERP / transformation sur l’ensemble du cycle (recueil des besoins, conception, tests, mise en production et adoption).Excellente capacité à animer des ateliers et à gérer les parties prenantes ; aisance avec des interlocuteurs de niveau Direction.Français courant et anglais professionnel (écrit/oral).Autonomie, adaptabilité et sens du concret : envie de structurer et d’améliorer nos modes de fonctionnement au fil de la croissance en France.Basé(e) en France avec le droit d’y travailler ; disponible pour des déplacements chez les clients selon les besoins.AtoutsExpérience sur des projets avec IFS Cloud / IFS ERP (Finance) ; certification IFS appréciée.Expérience sur d’autres solutions ERP majeures (SAP, Oracle, Microsoft Dynamics) dans un contexte Finance.Connaissance des sujets d’intégration, de migration de données et de reporting / analyse (dont définition de KPI et des besoins des rapports Finance).Expérience dans un ou plusieurs des secteurs suivants : Industrie manufacturière ; Énergie & services publics ; Services ; Construction & ingénierie ; Transport maritime & services portuaires ; Aéronautique & défense.Expérience de mentorat / coaching et contribution à des méthodes, standards et livrables réutilisables.\nPourquoi HOIST ?Vous avez envie d’avoir un impact concret chez vos clients, tout en évoluant dans un environnement bienveillant et exigeant ? Chez HOIST, vous rejoignez une équipe orientée client, qui accompagne des transformations ambitieuses, guidée par nos valeurs : Customer Focus, Excellence through Expertise, Care for our People et Innovation. Vous bénéficierez de flexibilité, d’autonomie, d’un collectif solide et du soutien d’une communauté internationale d’experts.\nComment postulerPostulez directement via l’annonce, ou contactez l’équipe recrutement pour un premier échange. Les candidatures sont acceptées en français ou en anglais ; à noter que le processus d’entretien se déroulera majoritairement en anglais.\nNous ne pourrons pas étudier les candidatures de personnes basées hors de France. Nous ne travaillons pas avec des agences de recrutement pour ce poste."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4409424358","title":"Senior Customer Engineer","company":"Alitheon","location":"Bellevue","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://fr.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-customer-engineer-at-alitheon-4409424358?position=42&pageNum=0&refId=PThZqpK24CgEfFC2RxTXvA%3D%3D&trackingId=K9wHG%2BhnXEHeXqq7NBktcQ%3D%3D","description":"FeaturePrint | Zero Trust for Physical Things™\nSenior Customer EngineerRemote | Full-Time\nWe're looking for experienced customer-focused engineers who combine technical depth with customer focus and empathy. People who thrive on supporting real customers, bridging the gap between what our customers need and what our technology can deliver. If you're someone who gets energized by customer success and wants to be the trusted technical advisor in the room, this role is for you.\nABOUT ALITHEONAlitheon has created something that didn’t exist before: a way to give every physical object its own unique, immutable, permanent identity—using nothing more than a photograph.Our patented FeaturePrint technology works like fingerprints for people, but for things. By reading the inherent micro-surface features of any object, we can register, identify, authenticate, and trace individual items at scale—without altering the product, disrupting the production line, or relying on tags, stickers, etchings, QR codes, blockchain, or any other proxy marker (visible or invisible).We are not competing in an existing category. We are defining a new one.Our technology enables 1-to-1, item-level serialization across industries where traceability, authenticity, and provenance aren’t just operational concerns—they’re existential ones: luxury goods, collectibles, healthcare, military, automotive, and aerospace.\nWHY THIS ROLE EXISTSAlitheon's technology is only as good as the customers who deploy it and the support they receive. We're building a category that didn't exist before, which means our customers are often breaking new ground with us. They face unfamiliar challenges, need to learn our technology deeply, and require a technical partner who truly understands their business and our capabilities.That partner is the Customer Engineer - someone who sits between our customer's success and our product's potential. You're the person customers trust to optimize integrations, solve issues, demonstrate value, and represent their needs back to our product team. You're not just answering tickets; you're enabling customers to achieve outcomes they couldn't achieve alone.That's why we're looking for you: someone who combines technical depth with genuine customer empathy, who gets energized by helping customers win, and who sees every interaction as an opportunity to build trust and advocacy.\nWHAT YOU’LL DOI - DURING THE SALES PROCESSDeliver live demonstrations, technical workshops, proof-of-concept engagements, and integration reviews to prospective customers to support our business development teams.Translate customer pain points and feature requests into well-structured engineering requirements and champion them through our product roadmap process.II – DURING CUSTOMER ONBOARDINGOwn the technical onboarding of new customers end-to-end: scoping integration requirements, presenting architecture approaches, and guiding their teams through implementation.Support customer implementations end-to-end: working with project managers in tracking milestones, managing risks, and reporting status to internal and external stakeholders.Design, document, and maintain integration patterns and deployment best practices that scale across the customer base.Build and maintain tooling, scripts, and automation that improve and reduce time-to-value.Design and deliver training and guidelines for customers’ own technical support and engineering teams, enabling them to self-serve on routine issues.Use and teach API documentation, SDK guides, and integration guides.III – ONGOING CUSTOMER SUPPORTOwn the relationship with customers, serving as their primary point of contact at Alitheon.Build and maintain tooling, scripts, and automation that improve customer outcomes.Conduct technical reviews of customer deployments to identify performance bottlenecks, configuration issues, and optimization opportunities.Act as the senior escalation point for complex technical issues that front-line support cannot resolve, performing root-cause analysis across application, infrastructure, and integration layers.Reproduce, diagnose, and resolve issues by analyzing logs, API responses, network traces, and system configurations - escalating to engineering with well-documented findings when necessary.Proactively identify systemic issues across the customer base and drive permanent fixes with engineering, rather than applying repeated workarounds.Contribute to API documentation, SDK guides, and integration guides based on real-world customer usage and common pitfalls.Test new features from a customer-deployment perspective before release, providing structured feedback to product and engineering.Build and maintain internal knowledge systems that capture technical learnings, troubleshooting playbooks, and customer context.\nWHO YOU ARERequired Qualifications, Capabilities, And Skills5+ years as the owner of customer-facing technical support, such as Solutions Architect, Technical Account Manager, Customer Engineer, or Implementation Engineer. Hands-on experience with REST APIs: you can read API documentation, construct requests, interpret responses, and debug integration issues independently.Comfortable and proficient in writing scripts (Python, Bash, PowerShell, or similar) to automate tasks, parse data, and reproduce issues.Working knowledge of cloud infrastructure, including deployment models, networking basics, and log analysis.Experience working at the intersection of software and hardware—you understand that not every problem is in the code, and you know how to troubleshoot across those boundaries.Strong technical communication skills: you can write a clear root-cause analysis, lead a technical workshop, and present to senior stakeholders with equal confidence.Able to manage and prioritize work across a portfolio of customers and projects simultaneously, exercising sound judgment on where to invest your time.Entrepreneurial energy. You thrive in a high-growth, often ambiguous environment where you’re building something, not maintaining it.Experience deploying or supporting cloud-hosted SaaS solutions in enterprise environments.Advantageous ExperienceBackground in machine vision, image processing, or computer vision technologies.Manufacturing floor operational technology, industrial integration, or IoT experience.\nWHY JOIN ALITHEONCustomer impact that matters. You're not just solving tickets—you're enabling customers to solve problems they couldn't solve before. From helping manufacturers prove provenance to helping healthcare organizations keep counterfeit drugs out of supply chains, your work has real consequences.Deep technical problems. You'll work with sophisticated customers deploying cutting-edge technology in complex environments. Every customer is breaking new ground, and you'll learn constantly.The voice of the customer. Your feedback directly shapes our product roadmap. You're not executing someone else's plan—you're influencing what we build next.Category creation. You're helping define how a brand new category gets built, not iterating on an existing one. Your early decisions and relationships will shape the industry.Build real relationships. You're not a handoff point—you're a trusted technical advisor.\n\nCOMPENSATION & STRUCTURECompensation is commensurate with experience and reflects the strategic nature of this role. This is a remote position with expected travel to industry events, client sites, and periodic company gatherings.\nReady to turn your industry expertise into the next chapter of your career?Send your resume and a brief note about the industry problems you’ve spent your career solving to info@alitheon.com. We’d rather hear your war stories than read a cover letter.\nAlitheon| alitheon.com |Fingerprints for Things™"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4404458542","title":"Senior Strategy Consultant","company":"Planview","location":"Austin","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://fr.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-strategy-consultant-at-planview-4404458542?position=12&pageNum=0&refId=PThZqpK24CgEfFC2RxTXvA%3D%3D&trackingId=p3pneBVKYK5L%2FrYB9g%2B0XQ%3D%3D","description":"Planview has one mission: to build the future of connected work, from ideas to impact.\nAs the global leader in work and resource management, Planview helps organizations accelerate the achievement of what matters most, supporting our customers from need to speed, from passion to progress, and from overhead to optimization. We provide the industry’s most comprehensive solutions designed for strategic planning, portfolio and resource management, Lean and Agile delivery, product portfolio management, capability, and technology management (enterprise architecture), innovation management, and collaborative work and project management. Our connected platform of solutions underpins the business and digital transformations of more than 4,500 customers globally, including 59 of the Fortune 100.\nAt Planview, our people connections drive our innovation and success. Our global team of 1400+ work remotely and across our offices including Austin, Vancouver, Hod Hasharon, Bangalore, Sydney, and Stockholm. We’re proud of our world-class, connected culture built on our shared values, that supports our teams to be successful from anywhere.\nLearn more about our portfolio at planview.com, and connect with us on LinkedIn, Instagram, and X.\nThe Opportunity\nWe are seeking a high-potential Senior Strategy Consultant to support executive transformation engagements across Europe.Working within Planview’s Global Enterprise Transformation team, you will help shape executive discussions with leading European enterprises through workshops, short engagements, strategic research, business case development, and transformation storytelling.This is a customer-facing advisory role, operating across both prospective and existing Planview customers.You will gain exposure to senior executives across major European organizations and collaborate with experienced strategists, sales leaders, transformation specialists and product teams to deliver high-impact executive engagements.Executive engagement at Planview is authentically focused on the clients’ transformation journey, but in service to sales of our analyst lauded and industry leading SaaS platform. This position offers exposure to diverse industries across Europe, including FTSE and DAX 100 clients, and collaborating with a team of experienced professionals.\nSpecial Project (First 3-6 months):You will lead the tailoring of our Transformation & Executive Engagement motion for the Central and Southern European region – adapting messaging, executive workshop design, and value narratives to regional market dynamics. Over time, you will increasingly own and scale this motion.\nWhat You'll Do\nExecutive & Transformation EngagementSupport the design and delivery of high-impact executive workshops for prospective and existing clientsConduct research and stakeholder analysis to understand client transformation challengesHelp facilitate transformation strategy engagements (~2–6 weeks)\nStrategy & Business Case DevelopmentDevelop executive-ready presentations and transformation roadmapsBuild CFO-quality business cases and value narrativesTranslate complex operational and strategic challenges into clear insights and recommendations\nSales & Growth SupportPartner with sales, solution, marketing, implementation and customer success teams to support strategic deal pursuitsContribute transformation narratives that align client priorities with Planview capabilitiesSupport account growth by identifying value expansion opportunities\nRegional Motion Development (Central & Southern Europe)Adapt transformation messaging and workshop formats for regional executive audiencesDevelop regionally relevant points of view and case examplesBuild reusable assets and playbooks to scale the motion\nThought Leadership & Insight DevelopmentContribute to transformation points of view combining industry trends, best practices, and Planview capabilitiesSupport development of executive-ready insights and workshop content\nWhat You'll Bring\nExperience4-6 years’ experience in management consulting, transformation delivery, or strategic advisoryExperience at a top-tier consulting firm or transformation practice strongly preferredExposure to operating model, digital transformation, portfolio management, or enterprise strategy work SkillsStrong executive storytelling capability, with excellent PowerPoint structuring and visualization skillsAdvanced Excel capability and experience building structured business casesAbility to synthesize complex qualitative and quantitative inputs into clear executive insightsStrong structured problem-solving capabilityEffective workshop facilitation, whiteboarding, and real-time synthesis skills (virtual and in-person)Experience leveraging AI tools to enhance consulting outputs and analytical workflows Mindset & AttributesStrong business acumen and curiosity about enterprise transformation and key trends impacting this (e.g. AI Operating Models)Comfortable working in fast-paced, client-facing environmentsAbility to collaborate across sales, strategy, services and product teamsHigh ownership mentality with a growth mindset\nEducationMaster’s degree preference or equivalent executive experience in business, economics, finance, informatics, technology\nOtherFluent English required; additional European languages a strong advantage - with German and / or French language skills particularly attractiveWillingness to travel regionally\nWhy This RoleDirect exposure to executive transformation discussions across major European enterprisesOpportunity to shape a regional transformation motionApply consulting skillset in a high-impact enterprise SaaS contextWork on complex strategy and operating model challenges across industriesCollaborate with experienced practitioners across strategy, transformation, and technology domains\nBenefits at Planview\nAt Planview, you’ll join our global team and culture which reflects the vibrant communities in which our employees live and work. To support you at Planview, you will enjoy:Unplugged Days: 4 company-wide paid days off per year to recharge and relax.Generous PTO offerings (region dependent).Region specific competitive benefit plans to support you at any life stage including parental leave, retirement, medical plans, wellness support, and remote work support.Paid time to volunteer through Planview’s Force for Good Week.Employee Referral bonus program.Weekly office lunches for hybrid team members and social events.Flexible work hours/environment.Now is a great time to join our team. If you are looking for a place to grow your career, innovate with best-in-class solutions, and build the future of connected work, Planview is the right place for you!\nDiversity, Equity and Inclusion at Planview\nAs part of our efforts to build a workforce with diverse talent, we encourage applications from Indigenous, Black, and other racialized communities, 2SLGBTQIA+ communities, people with neurodivergence, immigrants, people with disabilities, and other equity deserving groups. In addition to building a diverse workforce, we are committed to fostering an inclusive and accessible experience. Reasonable accommodations for the interview process can be requested by emailing recruitment@planview.com."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4407005510","title":"Director Analyst – Agentic AI in Enterprise Networking (Remote: Europe)","company":"Gartner","location":"Stamford","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://gartner.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com/EXT/job/Remote---United-Kingdom/Director-Analyst---Networking--Remote--Europe-_107687-1/apply?source=JB-10120","description":"About the role:\n\nGartner analysts are industry thought leaders who create must-have insight and provide advice to a broad range of world-leading organizations. A Director, Analyst possesses a keen eye for identifying gaps, problems and solutions within the market they serve, and help clients make better decisions relative to their highest business priorities. As an analyst, you will bring Gartner's best practices, and tools to life across a broad range of world class clients. Your focus will be on both the pragmatic content that assists a client in solving today’s problems, and provocative insight that challenges a client’s assumptions on how the future will play out.\n\nKey areas of coverage will be in agentic AI networking technologies that allow infrastructure and IT operations groups to drive automation, innovation, and lay the foundation for continued success and growth. Knowledge (and intellectual curiosity) in areas such as agentic AI, network operations, and network automation are important. You will apply your broad knowledge of technologies, vendors, processes, and best practices to provide actionable insights to our clients.\n\nWhat you will do:\n\nResearch, analyze and predict expected (and foresee unexpected) market trends and shifts to provide end-user organizations and vendors with actionable insights. Remain ahead of the curve on developments and issues within the specified areas as well as applicable adjacent areas of emerging technologies. Collaboratively write and publish analysis and positions at a regular cadence through evidence-based researchCommunicate complex concepts concisely and with authority via virtual or face-to-face interactions with senior-level executives. Present at multiple conferences as an industry expert. Partner with sales and service delivery partners to increase account growth, retention, and engagement\n\nWhat you will need:\n\nBachelor's degree or equivalent experience; graduate degree preferred. 12+ years of experience in enterprise networking, AI-driven network operations, or related IT domains, including hands-on exposure to the integration of AI and automation within large-scale enterprise network environments. Expertise in agentic AI models and AI‑enabled network architectures, including autonomous remediation, intent-based networking, policy orchestration, and AI-driven network optimization. Knowledge of agentic AI networking offerings from established vendors (e.g., Cisco, Fortinet, Palo Alto Networks and HPE) and emerging vendors (e.g., Aviz Networks, Selector.AI, Linkeye.ai, NetPrompt.ai, and Nanites.ai). Ability to analyze and articulate technology and business adoption scenarios, helping senior IT leaders understand the opportunities, risks, and implementation paths for emerging AI-centric networking technologies. Deep knowledge of enterprise networking technologies, including WAN connectivity, network architecture/design, network security principles, and strong familiarity with data center networking and cloud edge architectures. Strong working knowledge of SASE, SSE, NaaS, SD‑WAN, and evolving cloud connectivity paradigmsUnderstanding of networking‑specific security frameworks, including Zero‑Trust principles, identity-driven policy enforcement, and AI-enhanced detection and response models. Familiarity with global service provider offerings, major vendor ecosystems, and emerging AI‑native networking platforms and startups. Broad understanding of market and technology drivers, including cloud migration, distributed enterprise, edge computing, application modernization, and the evolving role of AI agents in autonomous enterprise infrastructure. \n\nWho are we? \n\nAt Gartner, Inc. (NYSE:IT), we guide the leaders who shape the world.\n\nOur mission relies on expert analysis and bold ideas to deliver actionable, objective business and technology insights, helping enterprise leaders and their teams succeed with their mission-critical priorities.\n\nSince our founding in 1979, we’ve grown to 21,000 associates globally who support ~14,000 client enterprises in ~90 countries and territories. We do important, interesting and substantive work that matters. That’s why we hire associates with the intellectual curiosity, energy and drive to want to make a difference. The bar is unapologetically high. So is the impact you can have here.\n\nWhat makes Gartner a great place to work? \n\nOur vast, virtually untapped market potential offers limitless opportunities – opportunities that may not even exist right now – for you to grow professionally and flourish personally. How far you go is driven by your passion and performance.\n\nWe hire remarkable people who collaborate and win as a team. Together, our singular, unifying goal is to deliver results for our clients.\n\nOur teams are inclusive and composed of individuals from different geographies, cultures, religions, ethnicities, races, genders, sexual orientations, abilities and generations.\n\nWe invest in great leaders who bring out the best in you and the company, enabling us to multiply our impact and results. This is why, year after year, we are recognized worldwide as a great place to work.\n\nWhat do we offer? \n\nGartner offers world-class benefits, highly competitive compensation and disproportionate rewards for top performers.\n\nIn our hybrid work environment, we provide the flexibility and support for you to thrive — working virtually when it's productive to do so and getting together with colleagues in a vibrant community that is purposeful, engaging and inspiring.\n\nReady to grow your career with Gartner? Join us.\n\nThe policy of Gartner is to provide equal employment opportunities to all applicants and employees without regard to race, color, creed, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, marital status, citizenship status, age, national origin, ancestry, disability, veteran status, or any other legally protected status and to seek to advance the principles of equal employment opportunity.\n\nGartner is committed to being an Equal Opportunity Employer and offers opportunities to all job seekers, including job seekers with disabilities. If you are a qualified individual with a disability or a disabled veteran, you may request a reasonable accommodation if you are unable or limited in your ability to use or access the Company’s career webpage as a result of your disability. You may request reasonable accommodations by calling Human Resources at +1 (203) 964-0096 or by sending an email to ApplicantAccommodations@gartner.com.\n\nJob Requisition ID:107687\n\nBy submitting your information and application, you confirm that you have read and agree to the country or regional recruitment notice linked below applicable to your place of residence.\n\nGartner Applicant Privacy Link: https://jobs.gartner.com/applicant-privacy-policy\n\nFor efficient navigation through the application, please only use the back button within the application, not the back arrow within your browser.\n\n"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4387118244","title":"Senior App Security Sales Executive","company":"GitHub","location":"San Francisco","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://githubinc.jibeapply.com/jobs/5168?lang=en-us&iis=Job+Board&iisn=LinkedIn&lever-source=LinkedinPosting","description":"About GitHub\n\nGitHub is the world’s leading platform for agentic software development — powered by Copilot to build, scale, and deliver secure software. Over 180 million developers, including more than 90% of the Fortune 100 companies, use GitHub to collaborate, and more than 77,000 organisations have adopted GitHub Copilot.\n\nLocations\n\nIn this role you can work from Remote, France\n\nOverview\n\nGitHub helps companies build better software together. We’re passionate about securing the world’s code and delivering a world‑class developer experience through industry‑leading, AI‑powered application security solutions.\n\nWe’re seeking results‑driven Application Security Sales Executive to accelerate adoption and growth of GitHub Advanced Security (GHAS) across our most strategic customers. This role blends strategic sales execution, deep application security expertise, and trusted technical engagement. You’ll operate as a customer‑facing subject matter expert—equally comfortable in executive conversations and deep technical discussions with security, platform, and developer teams.\n\nThis is a highly visible role for someone who is technically curious, customer‑obsessed, and motivated to drive real security and business outcomes.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nLead Technical & Strategic Engagements\n\nLead technical sales motions including discovery, demo, and proof‑of‑concepts (POCs).Deliver compelling customer presentations, clearly articulating value and addressing technical and business challenges in live settings.Serve as a trusted advisor, providing unique insights that help customers think differently about securing modern software development.Identify customer needs and map them to GitHub Advanced Security capabilities to influence buying decisions and progress opportunities through the sales lifecycle.\n\nDrive Growth & Adoption\n\nPartner with enterprise sales teams to develop and execute strategic account plans that drive GHAS adoption and revenue growth.Collaborate closely with GitHub and Microsoft stakeholders across sales, product, engineering, marketing, services, and support to ensure aligned execution and customer success.Act as the Voice of the Customer by capturing feedback, competitive insights, and emerging trends to inform product and roadmap decisions.Advocate for customer readiness and long‑term success through enablement, training, community engagement, and partner ecosystems.\n\nApplication Security Expertise\n\nAct as a subject matter expert on GitHub Advanced Security, including code scanning, secret scanning, software composition analysis, and AI‑powered remediation.Demonstrate strong understanding of application security concepts (SAST, DAST, SCA), vulnerability classes, and the broader AppSec market landscape..\n\nOperational Excellence\n\nMaintain strong pipeline health, forecasting accuracy, and disciplined execution across opportunities.Proactively identify and remove blockers, mitigate risk, and ensure a high‑quality end‑to‑end customer experience.\n\nWhat You Bring\n\nStrong application security domain knowledge and passion for securing modern software while improving developer experience.Proven experience in technical sales, security consulting, or security specialist roles ideally with mid-market or small business customers.Ability to translate complex security concepts into clear business value for both technical and executive audiences.A customer‑obsessed mindset with strong relationships‑building, curiosity, and empathy.Comfort operating as a trusted advisor and subject matter expert, internally and externally.Strong communication skills: verbal, written, and presentation while grounded in real‑world customer experience.Experience collaborating across diverse, cross‑functional teams to drive shared outcomes.Lead technical sales motions: discovery, demos, and POCsInfluence buying decisions by mapping customer needs to GitHub Advanced Security capabilitiesPartner with enterprise sales on strategic account plans to drive GHAS adoption and revenueAct as a trusted advisor delivering clear value-focused customer presentationsCollaborate with sales, product, engineering, marketing, and services to ensure customer successServe as Voice of the Customer, sharing feedback, competitive insights, and market trendsOperate as a GHAS subject matter expert (code scanning, secret scanning, SCA, AI remediation)Apply strong AppSec knowledge (SAST, DAST, SCA) with technical sales and consulting experienceBuild trusted relationships through strong communication, empathy, and customer focus\n\nQualifications\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\n6+ years experience in sales, pre-sales, technical consulting, or related fieldOR Bachelor's Degree in Business, Information Technology, or related field AND 4+ years experience in sales, pre-sales, technical consulting, or related field OR equivalent experience. 2+ years experience selling Developer Automation, Artificial Intelligence, CICD, Metered Developer Tools, DevOps, Application Security, or DevSecOps solutions. \n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n3+ years experience developing, collaborating, executing on go-to-market Will be working throughout all of EMEA, strongly prefer candidates with the ability to fluently speak, read, and write in French and English.\n\nGitHub values\n\nCustomer-obsessedShip to learnGrowth mindsetOwn the outcomeBetter togetherDiverse and inclusive\n\nManager fundamentals\n\nModelCoachCare\n\nLeadership principles\n\nCreate clarityGenerate energyDeliver success\n\nWho We Are\n\nGitHub is the world’s leading AI-powered developer platform with 150 million developers and counting. We’re also home to the biggest