eers on project deliveries to enable our customers to achieve the full potential of our industrial dataops platform.Conduct code reviews and implement best practices to ensure high-quality and maintainable code and deliveries.Support customers and partners in conducting data engineering tasks with Cognite products.Contribute to the development of Cognite’s official tools and SDKs.Collaborate with our Engineering and Product Management teams to turn customer needs into a prioritized pipeline of product offerings.\n\nThe Impact you bring to Cognite\n\nHave a DevOps mindset, and experience with Git, CI/CD, deployment environmentsEnjoys working in cross-functional teamsAble to independently investigate and solve problemsHumility to ask for help and enjoy sharing knowledge with others\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\nMinimum 3-5 years of relevant experience in a customer-facing Data intense roleExperience delivering production-grade data pipelines using e.g. Python, SQL and Rest APIsExperience with distributed computing such as Kubernetes and managed cloud services such as GCP and/or Azure\n\nPreferred Experience\n\nBachelor or Master degree in computer science or similar. Relevant experience can compensate for formal education\n\nEqual Opportunity\n\nCognite is committed to creating a diverse and inclusive environment at work and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive the same level of consideration for employment."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4407083121","title":"Regional Director, Middle East","company":"Harvard Business Publishing","location":"Brighton","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://hbpublishing.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/Careers/job/Remote-UAE/Regional-Director--Middle-East_JR260119?source=LinkedIn","description":"Harvard Business Publishing (HBP) – the leading destination for innovative management thinking. We reach lifelong learners to improve the practice of management in a changing world. This mission inspires each of us to unlock the leader in everyone – including you!\n\nThe opportunity\n\nAbout Organization:\n\nAt Harvard Business Impact, we are passionate about excellence in business education. We partner with Higher Education institutions, educators and students around the world to deliver best-in-class learning experiences that develop leaders who are ready for a changing world. We provide cases, simulations, articles, online courses, and emerging AI-enabled learning tools to higher education institutions worldwide. We support faculty and program leads through pedagogical support, teaching advice, and curriculum guidance to help them create dynamic and powerful learning moments that students will remember long after they leave the classroom.\n\nPosition Overview:\n\nHarvard Business Impact is seeking a dynamic and experienced Regional Director to lead and expand our presence across the Middle East higher education sector. This role calls for an accomplished commercial and relationship leader who can act as a player-coach—personally driving strategic opportunities while leading and developing a small regional team.\n\nThe Regional Director will own the regional strategy and performance for the Middle East, building trusted relationships internally and externally, orchestrating complex multi-stakeholder engagements, and collaborating across global teams. As the senior representative of Harvard Business Impact in the region, the Regional Director will play a critical role in shaping regional strategy, strengthening partnerships with leading institutions, and ensuring strong execution aligned with global priorities.\n\nThe Regional Director must be comfortable engaging at the highest levels—including chancellors, vice-chancellors, presidents, deans, senior government officials, and board-level decision makers—to support our expansion across the Middle East.\n\nThis role requires an entrepreneurial mindset, strong consultative selling expertise, and a passion for education, including the ability to advise institutions navigating rapid change in teaching, learning, and educational leadership, particularly the growing role of artificial intelligence in higher education. This is an opportunity to lead Harvard Business Impact’s growth in the Middle East and shape the future of higher education in the region.\n\nThe Regional Director will work closely with the Senior Director EMEA & APAC to shape regional growth strategy, expand market presence, and achieve revenue targets within the higher education sector.\n\nWhat You'll Do\n\nRegional Leadership & Market Development\n\nOwn and drive Harvard Business Impact’s growth across the Middle East region, identifying strategic opportunities and building long-term institutional partnershipsBuild and manage relationships with senior academic leaders and government stakeholders, including chancellors, presidents, deans, and ministry officialsDevelop and maintain a strong pipeline of partnerships and position HBI as a trusted long-term partner for universities navigating digital transformation and AI adoptionLead, mentor, and support a small regional team, fostering accountability, collaboration and alignment with global strategy\n\nSales Strategy & Strategic Engagement\n\nDevelop and execute the regional sales strategy to achieve revenue targets and expand HBI’s institutional footprintLead complex consultative engagements with universities and government institutions, aligning HBI’s solutions—including cases, simulations, articles, and digital learning offerings—to institutional needsGuide institutions through the full partnership journey, from initial engagement and solution design to negotiation and long-term collaboration\n\nCross-Functional Collaboration & Market Insight\n\nPartner with global teams across marketing, product, and customer success to ensure coordinated engagement and delivery of value to institutionsMonitor market trends, institutional priorities, and competitive dynamics to inform strategy and provide insights to internal leadershipRepresent Harvard Business Impact at key regional conferences, academic forums, and industry events to strengthen relationships and generate new opportunities.\n\nReporting & Strategic Alignment\n\nProvide regular updates on regional performance, pipeline development, and market insights to senior leadershipEnsure strong alignment between regional activities and HBI’s global strategy through transparent communication and collaboration\n\nWhat You’ll Bring\n\nMinimum of 10 years of experience in business development, partnerships, or commercial leadership within education, publishing, professional services, or related sectorsProven track record managing complex institutional sales cycles and building long-term partnerships with universities or government stakeholdersExperience developing and executing regional growth strategiesDemonstrated ability to build trusted relationships with senior academic leaders, institutional executives, and government stakeholdersEntrepreneurial mindset and ability to operate independently in a regional leadership roleExperience working within complex, hierarchical environments and negotiating high-value partnershipsAbility to operate as a player-coach, balancing hands-on engagement with leadership and development of a regional teamStrong collaboration and stakeholder-management skillsGrowth mindset, adaptability, and intellectual curiosityDeep understanding of Middle Eastern business culture and engagement practicesFamiliarity with higher-education systems and the evolving landscape of digital and active learning solutionsInterest in the impact of artificial intelligence and digital transformation in higher educationExcellent written and verbal communication skills in EnglishProficiency in Arabic or another regional language is highly desirableWillingness to travel within the Middle East region (approximately 50%)\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nAs a mission-driven global company, Harvard Business Publishing is committed to fostering a culture of inclusion, trust, and engagement where everyone is welcome, valued, respected, and feels they belong. In addition to a competitive compensation and benefits package, we offer meaningful programs focused on career development and employee wellness, such as education reimbursement and early-release Summer Fridays!\n\nHBP is an equal opportunity employer, and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, gender identity, sexual orientation, pregnancy and pregnancy-related conditions, or any other characteristic protected by law."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4409063477","title":"Business Development Representative MENA","company":"indaHash","location":"Dubai","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://indahash.applytojob.com/apply/oJRCM9krgo/Business-Development-Representative-MENA?source=LILI","description":"About IndaHash\n\nindaHash is a global influencer marketing platform connecting brands with over 5 million creators worldwide. We help brands run scalable, data-driven influencer campaigns across multiple markets, working with leading global brands and agencies.\n\nOur mission is simple: make influencer marketing smarter, faster, and more effective.\n\nAbout The Role\n\nWe’re looking for a proactive and hungry Business Development Representative to support our growth in the MENA market.\n\nThis role is perfect for someone early in their sales career who enjoys prospecting and hunting, meeting new people, spotting opportunities, and opening doors to new business. You’ll play a key role in building relationships with brands and agencies, identifying opportunities, and helping expand indaHash’s presence in the market.\n\nYou don’t need to have experience in influencer marketing -hunger to be self-motivated to grow the business, experience in advertising, media, digital marketing, or related industries is essential. You will also need to demonstrate previous success in generating new business revenue. What matters most is your drive to generate opportunities and grow business.\n\nWhat you’ll be doing\n\nIdentify and reach out to potential brand and agency partners in the GCC regionGenerate new business opportunities through outreach, networking, and researchBuild and maintain a strong pipeline of potential clientsQualify leads and support the Business Development team in turning opportunities into dealsCollaborate with internal teams to prepare pitches and proposals Track outreach, opportunities, and pipeline activity in CRM toolsStay up to date with trends in social media, influencer marketing, and the creator economy\n\nWho we’re looking for\n\n1-3 years of experience in sales, lead generation, or business developmentExperience in advertising, media, marketing, or digital industries (essential)Strong communication and relationship-building skillsA proactive mindset and confidence in reaching out to new contactsCommercial thinking and interest in the creator economyHungry, self-motivated and resilientFluent English and Arabic\n\nWhat makes you a great fit\n\nYou have proven experience in generating new businessYou enjoy building connections and opening conversationsYou’re curious about brands, campaigns, and how marketing worksYou’re organised and comfortable managing multiple opportunitiesYou’re motivated by results and growth \n\nWhy indaHash\n\nWork with global brands and international marketsBe part of the fast-growing creator economy spaceCollaborate with teams across multiple regionsGrow your career in business development and digital marketing Fully remote work environment\n\nindaHash, powered by ArabyAds, is the fastest growing technology platform that connects influencers from all over the world. Currently, indaHash operates in over 88 markets and owns offices in the United Arab Emirates, Singapore, Indonesia, Malaysia, the UK, South Africa and Poland. We cooperate with over 5,000,000 influencers and work with the biggest brands from the Fortune 500.\n\nSince 2016 indaHash has conducted more than 23 000 campaigns for the world’s largest brands (Coca-cola, McDonald’s, L’Oreal, Electrolux and many more) in over 88 markets. indaHash cooperates parallelly with media houses and advertising agencies from around the world to carry out effective global campaigns on Instagram, Facebook, Snapchat, Twitter, TikTok and many more.\n\nPowered by JazzHR\n\noJRCM9krgo"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4378383385","title":"Sales Director","company":"BeyondTrust","location":"Johns Creek","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/beyondtrust/jobs/7657490","description":"BeyondTrust is a place where you can bring your purpose to life through the work that you do, creating a safer world through our cybersecurity SaaS portfolio.\n\nOur culture of flexibility, trust, and continual learning means you will be recognized for your growth and for the impact you make on our success. You will be surrounded by people who challenge, support, and inspire you to be the best version of yourself.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe’re looking for a visible, driven, and strategic yet hands‑on sales leader who can elevate an already high‑performing team and accelerate our growth across Saudi Arabia. In this role, you’ll build and execute the GTM strategy to maximise and fast‑track our growth in Saudi Arabia.\n\nWe’re looking for a leader who is operationally excellent, able to hold the team accountable, and ensure accurate forecasting, disciplined pipeline management, and strong Salesforce hygiene.\n\nThis is a career‑defining opportunity for a leader who thrives in a high‑growth environment, blends strategic vision with hands‑on execution, and is passionate about driving impact at scale.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nIdentify, develop, and lead talent, including hiring and building a best-in-class team.Motivate and empower your team to drive revenue growth and profitability in alignment with company-wide objectives.Accurate quarterly sales forecasting and planning.Manage and motivate direct team by correlating performance expectations to business goals – including guiding account planning, proposal development, consistent performance feedback, etc.Create a culture of continuous improvement through ongoing performance analysis.Collaborate and work cross-functionally to provide insight to internal stakeholders across Product, Marketing, Analytics and Customer Success supporting product roadmap development.Develop and implement strategic sales plans. Take accountability for revenue growth and profit margins consistent with corporate objectives.Maintain up-to-date understanding of competitors' activities and competitive offerings.Provide negotiation assistance, training, and counselling to your team, in addition to assigning accounts, territories and sales quotas based on individual goals, capabilities, and pipeline activity.Identify and recommend business process improvements.\n\nWhat You’ll Bring\n\nMust be located in Saudi Arabia.5+ years’ hands-on sales leadership experience within the software security sector.Experience growing teams and revenue at a high-growth company across the defined territoryProven experience leading and developing software sales teams.Strong established relationships among key influencers within the Cyber Security Industry.Experience of analysing performance to identify areas of improvement/sales optimisation.Entrepreneurial mindset with a true sales hunter approachSound business judgment, intellectual discipline, self-confidence and a commitment to continual improvement.Excellent knowledge of SalesforceTech-savvy, with a passion for new technologies and up-to-date awareness of cybersecurity trends.Exceptional communication and negotiation skills.Highly organized and able to prioritize shifting responsibilities effectivelyAt ease working in a fast-paced environment to deliver results\n\nNice To Have\n\nCompleted sales training (Sandler, SPIN, DISC, TAS, Miller)\n\nBetter Together\n\nDiversity. Inclusion. They’re more than just words for us. They are the guiding values of how we build our teams, cultivate leaders, and create a culture where people feel connected.\n\nWe take care of our employees so they can take care of our customers. Customers who come from all walks of life just like us. We hire incredible people from diverse backgrounds because when we are different together, we are stronger together.\n\nAbout Us\n\nBeyondTrust is the global identity security leader protecting Paths to Privilege™. Our identity-centric approach goes beyond securing privileges and access, empowering organizations with the most effective solution to manage the entire identity attack surface and neutralize threats, whether from external attacks or insiders.\n\nBeyondTrust is leading the charge in transforming identity security to prevent breaches and limit the blast radius of attacks, while creating a superior customer experience and operational efficiencies. We are trusted by 20,000 customers, including 75 of the Fortune 100, and our global ecosystem of partners.\n\nLearn more at www.beyondtrust.com.\n\n"}
