{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4406547668","title":"Performance Marketing Creative Designer - Breakout","company":"Kraken","location":"Remote First","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/kraken.com/b9675e22-30a7-4e49-8cb9-385aa919b129/application?utm_source=LinkedIn","description":"Building the Future of Crypto \n\nOur Krakenites are a world-class team with crypto conviction, united by our desire to discover and unlock the potential of crypto and blockchain technology.\n\nWhat makes us different?\n\nKraken is a mission-focused company rooted in crypto values. As a Krakenite, you’ll join us on our mission to accelerate the global adoption of crypto, so that everyone can achieve financial freedom and inclusion. For over a decade, Kraken’s focus on our mission and crypto ethos has attracted many of the most talented crypto experts in the world.\n\nBefore you apply, please read the Kraken Culture page to learn more about our internal culture, values, and mission. We also expect candidates to familiarize themselves with the Kraken app. Learn how to create a Kraken account here.\n\nAs a fully remote company, we have Krakenites in 70+ countries who speak over 50 languages. Krakenites are industry pioneers who develop premium crypto products for experienced traders, institutions, and newcomers to the space. Kraken is committed to industry-leading security, crypto education, and world-class client support through our products like Kraken Pro, Desktop, Wallet, and Kraken Futures.\n\nBecome a Krakenite and build the future of crypto!\n\nProof of work\n\nBreakout\n\nBreakout is the fastest-growing crypto prop trading firm in the world, backed by Kraken - one of the longest-running and most trusted crypto exchanges, founded in 2011. We fund skilled crypto traders with real capital, take on the risk, and pay them a share of the profits. Since launching in November 2023, we have paid our traders over $38M and counting.\n\nWe are solving a trust problem in an industry that earned its bad reputation. Most prop firms change rules after the fact, deny payouts on technicalities, or disappear overnight. Breakout was built to be the opposite: consistent rules since day one, on-demand payouts 24/7, and the financial backing of a publicly known parent. That is why traders choose us, and it is why we are scaling fast.\n\nWhat makes us different?\n\nBreakout exists to give serious crypto traders access to meaningful capital without putting their personal savings on the line. We are obsessive about trader experience, rule transparency, and doing right by the people who trust us with their time and money. We move fast, ship constantly, and treat marketing as a core growth engine - not a support function.\n\nBefore you apply, spend some time on breakoutprop.com. Read the rules. Look at the public payout leaderboard. Join our Discord and scroll the #payouts channel. Our growth story is built on proof, and the proof is all there to see.\n\nKraken backs Breakout because they believe crypto prop is one of the biggest unlocks in the industry for the next decade. We are building the firm that defines the category.\n\nJoin us and help shape the future of crypto prop trading.\n\nThe team\n\nYou will own every piece of creative that drives Breakout’s paid acquisition - across every channel, every format, and every market we run in.\n\nReporting directly to the VP of Growth, and working shoulder-to-shoulder with our Performance Marketing Lead, you will produce, iterate, and scale creative across video, static, and motion for Meta, TikTok, YouTube, X, Reddit, programmatic, CTV, and anywhere else we can find our audience.\n\nThis is a full-stack creative role. One day you are cutting a punchy 15-second TikTok using Veo 3 and Runway. The next you are designing a static Meta campaign in 12 localisations. The day after, you are building a motion-heavy YouTube pre-roll from scratch in After Effects. You set the bar for what Breakout’s performance creative looks, sounds, and feels like.\n\nWe are looking for someone who is both hands-dirty and strategically sharp. Someone fluent in the Adobe suite, already working with the latest AI creative tools, and who treats creative as a performance lever - not a brand exercise. You care about CTRs and CPAs as much as you care about craft.\n\nThis is a pure individual contributor role - not a manager role. You are here to make the work, not to direct others doing it. And you are not doing it in isolation. Alongside working directly within the Breakout growth team, you will also work directly with Payward’s (Kraken’s) performance marketing team - one of the leading paid acquisition operations in crypto. You will trade frameworks, channel learnings, and live test results back and forth, lean on their data and platform relationships where they accelerate what you are doing at Breakout, and share back the insights that can help the wider group. Your wins compound across Kraken’s brands, and theirs compound back to yours.\n\nThe opportunity\n\nOwn end-to-end creative production for every performance marketing channel Breakout runs - video, static, motion, carousel, display, CTV, everything.Develop, edit, and produce 30+ performance marketing creatives per month, tailored to platform, audience, and market. Velocity matters as much as quality.Collaborate with Performance Marketing, Brand, Content, and regional teams to turn ideas and tests into shipped assets fast.Work directly with Payward’s (Kraken’s) performance marketing team to trade creative insights, learn from the tests that have worked across their brands, and share the AI-native workflows you build at Breakout. One of the largest paid acquisition programs in crypto is on the other end of Slack, and you will use it.Leverage AI creative tools (Veo 3, Runway, Pika, Midjourney, Sora, ElevenLabs, and whatever ships next) as a core part of your workflow, not a novelty.Design static and motion ad creatives that perform - Meta carousels, TikTok hooks, Reddit static units, YouTube pre-roll, display banners, CTV spots, and anything the channel mix demands.Build scalable templates, style systems, and localisation workflows so we produce more, faster, in more markets, without losing consistency.Partner with Performance Marketing and Analytics to run creative A/B tests and iterate based on performance data. Your job is making ads that work.Maintain brand consistency across every asset, channel, and region - while flexing format and tone for the platform.Stay ahead on AI creative advancements, generative tools, emerging ad formats, and platform-native creative trends. Bring ideas. Try them. Share what works.Be scrappy and resourceful. We would rather ship ten rough tests and learn than polish one hero asset for a month.Train the team on new tools, new techniques, and workflows they did not know existed. Set the standard for how AI-native creative production runs at Breakout.Additional duties and responsibilities as assigned.\n\nSkills You Should HODL\n\nExpert-level proficiency across the Adobe Creative Suite (Premiere Pro, After Effects, Photoshop, Illustrator, Audition) and Figma.Deep hands-on experience with AI creative tools: Veo 3, Runway, Pika, Midjourney, Sora, ElevenLabs, Synthesia, and the broader AI-native stack. You were using these before your team knew they existed.Strong understanding of performance marketing creative - what stops a thumb, what kills a scroll, how platform-native creative differs from brand work.Proven ability to produce high-quality video, static, and motion creative across multiple formats, markets, and languages at speed.Strong design fundamentals: typography, composition, hierarchy, colour. You can make a static Meta ad that punches, not just a video that looks cool.Self-driven and motivated to constantly explore, learn, and experiment with emerging tech.Sharp creative instincts backed by data-driven iteration. You can read a performance dashboard and translate what it says into what to make next.Skilled at storytelling through motion, audio, and design, with obsessive attention to detail.Thrives as a pure individual contributor. You own creative output end-to-end, you have no interest in managing others, and you want to stay deep in the craft.Thrives in a fast-paced, global, remote environment. You would rather ship than debate.Passion for crypto, prop trading, and the future of finance - or at minimum, strong curiosity and the willingness to get deep on the audience fast.\n\nNice to haves\n\nExperience with 3D and motion graphics (Cinema 4D, Blender, Unreal Engine).Experience producing creative for CTV, long-form ad formats, and YouTube.Familiarity with sound design, AI voiceover, and localisation workflows at scale.Prior work on affiliate and partner-driven performance campaigns.\n\nUnless a specific application deadline is stated in the job posting, applications are accepted on an ongoing basis.\n\nPlease note, applicants are permitted to redact or remove information on their resume that identifies age, date of birth, or dates of attendance at or graduation from an educational institution.\n\nWe consider qualified applicants with criminal histories for employment on our team, assessing candidates in a manner consistent with the requirements of the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance.\n\nKraken is powered by people from around the world and we celebrate all Krakenites for their diverse talents, backgrounds, contributions and unique perspectives. We hire strictly based on merit, meaning we seek out the candidates with the right abilities, knowledge, and skills considered the most suitable for the job. We encourage you to apply for roles where you don't fully meet the listed requirements, especially if you're passionate or knowledgable about crypto!\n\nWe may ask candidates to complete job-related skills or work-style assessments as part of our hiring process. These assessments are designed to evaluate competencies relevant to the role and are applied consistently across candidates for similar positions. Assessment results are considered alongside other relevant information, such as experience and interviews, and are not the sole basis for any employment decision.\n\nAs an equal opportunity employer, we don’t tolerate discrimination or harassment of any kind. Whether that’s based on race, ethnicity, age, gender identity, citizenship, religion, sexual orientation, disability, pregnancy, veteran status or any other protected characteristic as outlined by federal, state or local laws.\n\nStay in the know\n\nFollow us on Twitter\n\nLearn on the Kraken Blog\n\nConnect on LinkedIn\n\nCandidate Privacy Notice\n\n"}
