s the door, Partner Solutions figures out what's actually behind it — breaking down ambiguous goals, designing the full solution, and staying engaged through to launch.\n\nThe opportunity\n\nLead and build the Partner Solutions function — the team brought in on the hardest, most ambitious partner engagementsOwn the end-to-end solution design process: from partner discovery and problem decomposition through to implementation oversight and go-live handoffShape how Payward Services goes to market — your team's pattern recognition across partner problems directly informs our propositions, packaging, and positioningArchitect full partner solutions across product scope, commercial model, operational structure, and regulatory design — not just the product layerPartner with Legal, Compliance, Product, and Engineering without needing hand-holding in any one domainCo-author the Solution Blueprint alongside Solutions Engineering, giving Implementation everything needed to executeDrive a clean handoff to Customer Success at go-live, so CSMs inherit a fully documented relationship\n\nSkills You Should HODL\n\nExtensive experience in fintech partnerships, strategy consulting, solutions design, or partner operations — ideally in regulated financial services or platform businessesExperience building and leading a teamProven ability to take complex, ambiguous partner problems and break them into structured, actionable solutionsTrack record of advising clients or partners through build decisions, helping them understand what they need, not just what you'll deliverCommercial instinct — you can model fee economics, pressure-test deal structures, and recognise when something doesn't pencilOperator mindset — you think about how things work day-to-day, not just how they look in a contractStrong cross-functional fluency across legal, compliance, product, and engineeringComfort with ambiguity — many of the playbooks don't exist yet, and you'll be writing them\n\nNice to haves\n\nExperience 