{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4407569247","title":"Haemato-Oncology Medical Scientific Liaison (MSL)","company":"GSK","location":"London","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.gsk.com/jobs/439364?lang=en-us&source=LinkedIn","description":"Site Name: Jeddah Headquarters Business Park, Riyadh Olaya Towers\n\nPosted Date: Apr 28 2026\n\nWe manufacture and supply reliable, high-quality medicines and vaccines to meet patients’ needs and drive our performance. Our network of 37 medicines and vaccines manufacturing sites delivered 1.7 billion packs of medicines and 409 million vaccine doses in 2024 to help make a positive impact on the health of millions of people. Our supply chain is not just core to our operations; it’s vital to bringing our innovations to patients as quickly, efficiently and effectively as possible. Technology is transforming how we manufacture medicines and vaccines, enabling us to increase the speed, quality and scale of product supply. We need the very best minds and capability to help us on our journey to make more complex products, harnessing the power of smart manufacturing technologies including robotics, digital solutions and artificial intelligence to deliver for patients.\n\nHaemato-Oncology Medical Scientific Liaison\n\nYou will be a field-based Haemato-Oncology Medical Scientific Liaison supporting medical engagement across Saudi Arabia. You will build trusted, scientific relationships with haematology and oncology experts. You will gather and share medical insights to shape evidence generation and medical strategy. We value clear communicators who work well across teams and who are motivated by making a real difference for patients. This role offers growth through exposure to clinical development, cross-functional projects, and opportunities to influence care in line with GSK’s mission to unite science, technology and talent to get ahead of disease together. The Medical Scientific Liaison (MSL) is a non-promotional field-based medical role responsible for conducting medical engagements/activities that ensure the safe and effective use of GSK’s medicines while generating medical insights. MSL is expected to drive EEs/HCPs education journeys using the behavior adoption tool, provide support to GSK clinical development & Key Evidence Generation programs.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nThis role will provide YOU the opportunity to lead key activities to progress YOUR career. These responsibilities include some of the following:\n\n\n Conduct peer-to-peer scientific interactions with haemato and oncology healthcare professionals, both proactively and reactively. Capture, document and share medical insights to inform local evidence generation and medical strategy. Support medical education activities, advisory boards, and scientific workshops for external experts and internal colleagues. Provide timely, fair and evidence-based responses to unsolicited medical information requests and safety queries. Support clinical development activities such as investigator identification and site feasibility when required. Use approved systems to record activities and outcomes, and ensure compliance with local laws, policies and pharmacovigilance requirements.\n\n\nWhy You?\n\nBasic Qualification\n\nWe are seeking professionals with the following required skills and qualifications to help us achieve our goals:\n\n\n Bachelor’s degree in pharmaceutical science. Saudi National Valid license from the Saudi Commission for Health Specialties or equivalent local licensure. At least 2 years’ experience in pharmaceutical medical, clinical, or field roles. Practical knowledge of haemato-oncology clinical practice or experience working with oncology or haematology healthcare professionals. Strong written and spoken English. Arabic is an advantage. Excellent communication skills and experience presenting clinical data to healthcare audiences.\n\n\nPreferred Qualification\n\nIf you have the following characteristics, it would be a plus\n\n\n Advanced degree ( PhD, or MSc) or postgraduate training in hematology, oncology, or related area. Experience supporting clinical trials, investigator identification, or site engagement. Familiarity with medical information systems and CRM platforms. Experience in evidence generation, publications, or health economics and outcomes research. Experience working within a matrix environment and collaborating with commercial, access, and regulatory teams. Fluency in Arabic and experience engaging national stakeholders, payers or guideline committees.\n\n\nWork Model\n\nThis role will be based in Saudi Arabia and is field-based with regular travel across the assigned geography. The role is on-site and hybrid working arrangements may be agreed based on business needs and local policy.\n\nHow to apply\n\nIf this role speaks to your skills and goals, we encourage you to apply. Tell us how your experience in haemato-oncology and scientific engagement will help patients and teams succeed. We look forward to hearing from you.\n\nنقوم بتصنيع وتوريد أدوية ولقاحات موثوقة وعالية الجودة لتلبية احتياجات المرضى وتعزيز أدائنا. سلَّمت شبكتنا المكوّنة من 37 موقعًا لإنتاج الأدوية واللقاحات ما مجموعه 1.7 مليار عبوة أدوية و409 مليون جرعة لقاح في عام 2024، مساهمةً في تحقيق أثر إيجابي على صحة ملايين الأشخاص. سلسلة التوريد لدينا ليست مجرد عنصر أساسي في عملياتنا؛ بل هي حيوية لإيصال ابتكاراتنا إلى المرضى بأسرع شكل ممكن وبكفاءة وفاعلية. تعمل التكنولوجيا على تحويل طريقة تصنيع الأدوية واللقاحات، مما يتيح لنا زيادة سرعة وجودة وحجم التوريد. نحتاج أفضل العقول والقدرات لمساندتنا في رحلتنا نحو تصنيع منتجات أكثر تعقيدًا، مستفيدين من قوة تقنيات التصنيع الذكي بما في ذلك الروبوتات، والحلول الرقمية، والذكاء الاصطناعي لخدمة المرضى.\n\nمنسق علمي طبي — أمراض الدم والأورام (Haemato‑Oncology Medical Scientific Liaison)\n\nستكون منسقًا علميًا طبيًا ميدانيًا في مجال أمراض الدم والأورام، تدعم التواصل الطبي عبر المملكة العربية السعودية. ستبني علاقات علمية موثوقة مع خبراء أمراض الدم والأورام، وستجمع وتشارك الرؤى الطبية للمساهمة في تشكيل جهود توليد الأدلة والاستراتيجية الطبية. نُقدّر أصحاب التواصل الواضح الذين يعملون بفاعلية عبر الفرق والذين يتحفّزون لإحداث فرق حقيقي للمرضى. يوفر هذا الدور فرصًا للنمو من خلال التعرض لتطوير الدراسات السريرية، المشاريع متعددة التخصصات، وفرص التأثير على الرعاية بما يتماشى مع مهمة GSK في توحيد العلم والتكنولوجيا والمواهب للتقدّم على الأمراض معًا.\n\nالمسؤوليات\n\nيوفر هذا الدور لك الفرصة لقيادة أنشطة رئيسية لتطوير مسارك المهني. تشمل بعض المسؤوليات ما يلي:\n\n\nإجراء تفاعلات علمية بين النظراء مع مختصي أمراض الدم والأورام، بشكل استباقي واستجابي.جمع وتوثيق ومشاركة الرؤى الطبية لإثراء جهود توليد الأدلة المحلية والاستراتيجية الطبية.دعم أنشطة التعليم الطبي، مجالس الاستشارة (advisory boards)، وورش العمل العلمية للخبراء الخارجيين والزملاء الداخليين.تقديم ردود مبنية على الأدلة وفي الوقت المناسب على طلبات المعلومات الطبية غير الموجّهة واستفسارات السلامة.دعم أنشطة التطوير السريري مثل تحديد المحققين ودراسة جدوى المواقع عند الحاجة.استخدام الأنظمة المعتمدة لتسجيل الأنشطة والنتائج، وضمان الامتثال للقوانين المحلية والسياسات ومتطلبات اليقظة الدوائية (Pharmacovigilance).\n\n\nلماذا أنت؟\n\nالمؤهلات الأساسية نبحث عن محترفين يمتلكون المهارات والمؤهلات التالية لمساعدتنا في تحقيق أهدافنا:\n\n\nالصيدلة.ترخيص ساري من الهيئة السعودية للتخصصات الصحية.خبرة لا تقل عن سنتين في أدوار طبية أو سريرية أو ميدانية في قطاع الأدوية.معرفة عملية بممارسات الرعاية السريرية في أمراض الدم والأورام أو خبرة في العمل مع مختصي الأورام أو أمراض الدم.إجادة قوية للغة الإنجليزية كتابةً ومحادثة؛ تُعتبر اللغة العربية ميزة.مهارات تواصل ممتازة وخبرة في عرض البيانات السريرية أمام جمهور من المتخصصين في الرعاية الصحية.\n\n\nالمؤهلات المفضلة\n\nإن توافرت لديك الخصائص التالية فستكون ميزة:\n\n\nشهادة متقدمة أو تدريب متخصص في أمراض الدم أو الأورام أو مجال ذي صلة.خبرة في دعم التجارب السريرية، تحديد المحققين أو التواصل مع مواقع البحث.إلمام بأنظمة المعلومات الطبية ومنصات إدارة علاقات العملاء (CRM).خبرة في توليد الأدلة، النشر العلمي، أو أبحاث اقتصاديات الصحة ونتائج الرعاية.خبرة العمل ضمن بيئة مصفوفية والتعاون مع فرق تجارية، فرق الوصول (access) والجهات التنظيمية.إجادة اللغة العربية وخبرة في التواصل مع أصحاب المصلحة الوطنيين أو دافعي التكلفة أو لجان وضع الإرشادات.\n\n\nنموذج العمل\n\nسيكون هذا الدور ميدانيًا ومقرّه المملكة العربية السعودية، ويتطلب سفرًا منتظمًا ضمن المنطقة المخصصة. الدور يتطلب تواجدًا ميدانيًا، ويمكن الاتفاق على ترتيبات عمل هجينة حسب احتياجات العمل والسياسة المحلية.\n\nكيفية التقديم\n\nإذا كان هذا الدور يتوافق مع مهاراتك وأهدافك، نشجعك على التقديم. أخبرنا كيف ستسهم خبرتك في أمراض الدم والأورام والتواصل العلمي في دعم المرضى والفرق على النجاح. نتطلع لسماعك.\n\nWhy GSK?\n\nUniting science, technology and talent to get ahead of disease together.\n\nGSK is a global biopharma company with a purpose to unite science, technology and talent to get ahead of disease together. We aim to positively impact the health of 2.5 billion people by the end of the decade, as a successful, growing company where people can thrive. We get ahead of disease by preventing and treating it with innovation in specialty medicines and vaccines. We focus on four therapeutic areas: respiratory, immunology and inflammation; oncology; HIV; and infectious diseases – to impact health at scale.\n\nPeople and patients around the world count on the medicines and vaccines we make, so we’re committed to creating an environment where our people can thrive and focus on what matters most. Our culture of being ambitious for patients, accountable for impact and doing the right thing is the foundation for how, together, we deliver for patients, shareholders and our people.\n\nContact information:\n\nYou may apply for this position online by selecting the Apply now button.\n\nImportant notice to Employment businesses/ Agencies\n\nGSK does not accept referrals from employment businesses and/or employment agencies in respect of the vacancies posted on this site. All employment businesses/agencies are required to contact GSK's commercial and general procurement/human resources department to obtain prior written authorization before referring any candidates to GSK. The obtaining of prior written authorization is a condition precedent to any agreement (verbal or written) between the employment business/ agency and GSK. In the absence of such written authorization being obtained any actions undertaken by the employment business/agency shall be deemed to have been performed without the consent or contractual agreement of GSK. GSK shall therefore not be liable for any fees arising from such actions or any fees arising from any referrals by employment businesses/agencies in respect of the vacancies posted on this site.\n\n"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4330663382","title":"Data Team Lead/Senior Data Team Lead","company":"IQVIA","location":"Durham","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.iqvia.com/jobs/R1510025-5?source=LinkedIn_Slots&amp;utm_source=linkedin.com&amp;utm_medium=job_posting","description":"JOIN US ON OUR EXCITING JOURNEY!\n\nIQVIA™ is The Human Data Science Company™, focused on using data and science to help healthcare clients find better solutions for their patients. Formed through the merger of IMS Health and Quintiles, IQVIA offers a broad range of solutions that harness advances in healthcare information, technology, analytics and human ingenuity to drive healthcare forward.\n\nThis Clinical Data Team Lead will be responsible for managing end-to-end delivery of data management services for single/multi-service projects, ensuring quality deliverables on time and within budget, to customer satisfaction. Provide comprehensive data management expertise to Clinical Data Management (CDM) team to provide high quality data management products that meet customer needs. Direct the team in areas of project planning, execution and close-out, financial management, communications and milestone deliverables. Comply with Good Clinical Practices (GCPs), applicable regulatory guidelines, SOPs, policies, and, where available, CDM guidance documents.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nClient Management\n\nServe as primary point of contact for customer on clinical data management deliverablesProvide project management expertise working with customer data managers, key decision makers, and internal team members to manage continuous process improvements, issue escalation, workload projections, and provide technical expertiseProvide justification for and perform direct negotiations with customer, e.g., timelines, financial, process, resourceMaintain strong customer relationshipsEnsure open communications with customer and Quintiles management to manage and meet contractual obligations\n\nService Management\n\nMeet with Data Operations Coordinator (DOC) and/or Data Operations team members on a regular basis to ensure milestones meet timelines and quality deliverablesEstablish strong communications with Data Operations team, functional leads, project managers and all other stake holdersSupport DM service delivery with comprehensive DM process and technical expertise in executing projectsServe as the escalation point for unresolved data issues; work with client data managers, vendors, and internal team members for resolutionWork with functional manager(s) to ensure appropriate resources are assigned to meet project deliverablesCreate and/or review and sign-off on all data management plan (DMP) documentsImplement proactive quality management plans across multiple projects/programme. Track service performance and provide leadership to identify root causes of issues and implement remedial actionsServe as Subject Matter Expert (SME)Provide leadership and expertise in a specific CDM task or technologyMaintain internal tracking databases and systems\n\nQualifications\n\nBachelor’s Degree, or educational equivalent, in health, clinical, biological or mathematical sciences, or related field5+ years direct Clinical Data Management experience in CRO or pharmaceuticals industry , including 3+ years as a CDM project lead; or equivalent combination of education, training and experiencePrevious experience and proven competence in managing delivery of multiple projects through full DM life-cycle (several studies/programmes)Previous experience of handling customer negotiationsKnowledge of Good Clinical Practices and relevant regulatory guidelinesExcellent communication, interpersonal, customer service, and teamwork skillsComprehensive understanding of clinical drug development processAbility to establish and maintain effective working relationships with co-workers, managers and customers\n\nIQVIA is a leading global provider of clinical research services, commercial insights and healthcare intelligence to the life sciences and healthcare industries. We create intelligent connections to accelerate the development and commercialization of innovative medical treatments to help improve patient outcomes and population health worldwide. Learn more at https://jobs.iqvia.com\n\nIQVIA is committed to integrity in our hiring process and maintains a zero tolerance policy for candidate fraud. All information and credentials submitted in your application must be truthful and complete. Any false statements, misrepresentations, or material omissions during the recruitment process will result in immediate disqualification of your application, or termination of employment if discovered later, in accordance with applicable law. We appreciate your honesty and professionalism.\n\n"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4408258707","title":"Head of Operations UAE","company":"BTSE","location":"Victoria","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.lever.co/BTSE/210f5cb6-ccc1-4185-9b2c-19cac1333717/?source=LinkedIn&lever-source=LinkedIn","description":"BTSE Group is a global leader in fintech and blockchain technology, anchored by three core business pillars: Exchange, Payments, and Infrastructure Development. Serving over 100 corporate clients worldwide, we provide white-label exchange and payment solutions. Our offerings encompass everything from exchange infrastructure hosting and development to custody, wallets, payments, blockchain integration, trading, and more.\n\nBTSE has pioneered multiple trading technologies that have been widely adopted across the industry, establishing new benchmarks for innovation, performance, and security in digital asset trading. Consistently ranked among the top 10 global exchanges, BTSE is expanding rapidly and invites ambitious, driven professionals to become valuable members of its B2C and B2B businesses.\n\nAbout The Opportunity\n\nWe are seeking a Head of Operations to lead the Dubai entity’s operations. This role will oversee day-to-day activities, establish operational frameworks, and support regulatory compliance and licensing.\n\nThe successful candidate must meet VARA's fit and proper standards, including demonstrated integrity, relevant industry experience, an understanding of the virtual asset regulatory framework, and financial soundness\n\nResponsibilities\n\n Oversee daily operations across trading, payments, and client lifecycle.  Establish and maintain operational processes, controls, and monitoring frameworks.  Support licensing and act as a key point of contact for regulators, including VARA.  Ensure alignment with compliance, risk, and internal policies.  Identify and manage operational risks, including incident handling and escalation.  Collaborate with global teams and provide regular reporting to senior management.  Support hiring and build-out of the local operations function. \n\nRequirements\n\n Proven track record of operations experience in financial services, fintech, or VASP.  Experience in a regulated environment with ownership of operational controls, policies and procedures.  Working knowledge of trading operations, payments, or client-facing operations workflows.  Familiarity with the UAE regulatory landscape, particularly VARA requirements, is strongly preferred.  Ability to meet VARA fit and proper requirements.  UAE resident or national,UAE-based or able to relocate.  Strong interpersonal communication and stakeholder management skills across internal teams, regulators and external partners. \n\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.\n\n"}
