{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4406905865","title":"Director of Business Development (Global / MENA Focus)","company":"UNLOCKLAND","location":"San Francisco","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://sa.linkedin.com/jobs/view/director-of-business-development-global-mena-focus-at-unlockland-4406905865?position=2&pageNum=0&refId=mx%2FsL6mZvEUCpV30zWu6zA%3D%3D&trackingId=YasTzSlYs6YwjBASujiKMQ%3D%3D","description":"UnlockLand is an AI-driven PropTech company recognized as one of the top innovators in the “Future of Lifestyle” PropTech Accelerator, led by the National Information Technology Development Program (NITDP) and the Real Estate General Authority (REGA) under Saudi Vision 2030.\n Our mission is to transform how developers, investors, and governments plan, evaluate, and optimize real-estate assets. \nUnlockLand’s AI Operating System integrates geospatial data, financial modelling, and regulatory intelligence to deliver instant feasibility studies and predictive analytics — helping cities and investors build smarter, more sustainable communities.\nRole SummaryAs Director of Business Development, you will lead enterprise and government growth for UnlockLand—owning the full commercial lifecycle from strategic outreach to signed partnerships and long-term expansion. You will build a high-quality pipeline across developers, institutional investors, ministries, planning authorities, and large-scale real estate programs, and translate market demand into actionable product and go-to-market priorities.\nKey Responsibilities (Elaborated)1. Enterprise & Government Revenue GrowthOwn and scale UnlockLand’s revenue pipeline across enterprise clients and public-sector stakeholders.Build relationships with developers, investors, REITs, consultants, and government entities to drive platform adoption.Lead complex, multi-stakeholder deal cycles from discovery to negotiation, contracting, and close.2. Strategic Partnerships & National ProgramsIdentify and structure partnerships with ministries, regulators, planning authorities, accelerators, and strategic ecosystem players.Develop partnership frameworks for pilots, city-scale deployments, and nationwide initiatives aligned with Vision 2030 objectives.Coordinate proposal development, MoUs, and commercial agreements with government and enterprise counterparts.3. Go-To-Market Strategy & Market ExpansionBuild and execute GTM plans for priority regions and sectors (e.g., residential, mixed-use, infrastructure, industrial).Develop segmentation strategies, ICPs, and value propositions tailored to different buyer types (developers vs. ministries vs. institutional capital).Create scalable playbooks for entering new markets, including pricing assumptions, implementation pathways, and success metrics.4. Product Commercialization & Solution SellingTranslate client needs into product requirements—helping shape modules around feasibility, zoning/regulatory intelligence, and predictive analytics.Run high-impact product demos and executive workshops that quantify ROI (time saved, risk reduction, capital efficiency).Package offerings into clear solution tiers (pilot → enterprise → national deployment) with measurable outcomes.5. Pipeline Management & Performance ExecutionBuild forecasting discipline: maintain CRM hygiene, pipeline velocity tracking, and conversion improvement.Define commercial KPIs (meetings, qualified pipeline, win rate, ACV, sales cycle, renewal/expansion).Partner with Marketing to drive demand generation through events, thought leadership, and targeted ABM.6. Executive Stakeholder ManagementWork closely with the CEO and leadership team on strategic accounts, board-level opportunities, and investor-facing growth narratives.Represent UnlockLand at industry forums, government meetings, and innovation summits as a trusted commercial leader.Support partnership governance post-close to ensure adoption, renewals, and expansion.\nIdeal ProfileThe ideal Director of Business Development is a strategic, relationship-driven commercial leader with:8–15+ years in business development, enterprise sales, partnerships, or GTM leadership (PropTech, real estate, SaaS, AI, fintech, or infrastructure).Proven success closing complex enterprise and/or public-sector deals with multiple stakeholders and long sales cycles.Strong familiarity with real estate development economics (feasibility, entitlements, underwriting, capital stacks) and the workflows of developers/investors.Experience engaging ministries, regulators, planning authorities, or national transformation programs (Vision 2030 experience is a major plus).Ability to sell technical platforms with clarity—communicating product value to both executives and technical stakeholders.A builder mindset: comfortable creating playbooks, partnerships, pricing, packaging, and repeatable growth systems from scratch.Passion for AI-driven transformation, smarter cities, and scaling real estate intelligence globally.\nWhat Success Looks Like (First 6–12 Months)Build a prioritized pipeline of high-value enterprise and government opportunities.Close landmark partnerships (pilot + enterprise contract structure) and establish repeatable pathways for expansion.Implement a scalable BD operating system: CRM process, pipeline reporting, and GTM playbooks.Establish UnlockLand as a trusted partner in AI-enabled planning and feasibility for developers and governments.\n"}
