n IT, telecommunications, or digital services.Technical background is preferred.Strong understanding of technology and how it supports client business objectives.Proficient in consultative sales methodologies, including prospecting, qualification, closure, and client satisfaction.Comfortable working in a highly matrixed, cross-functional, and global business environment.Experience in building and maintaining a professional network across varied lines of business.Leading PeopleBuilds strong team: Selects talent for skills and potential, ensures smooth onboarding, and builds trust and collaboration.Provides vision & direction: Communicates vision and team priorities clearly, ensuring understanding and alignment.Develops talent: Gives regular coaching, feedback, and guidance, supporting development and growth.Drives performance: Sets measurable team goals, monitors progress, resolves obstacles, and ensures accountability.Leads others through change: Anticipates team changes, communicates purpose, and coaches others to adopt new ways of working.Ensures SoftServe values are lived by: Addresses behaviors inconsistent with values and fosters a respectful, inclusive team environment.Leading BusinessFocuses on client: Understands client business and goals, builds trust across multiple functions, and consistently exceeds expectations.Understands business: Uses financials and market insights to guide decisions and align team actions.Thinks strategically: Contributes ideas that support team-level goals and adapts to emerging challenges.Thinks & acts globally: Adapts communication and behavior to different cultural contexts and collaborates effectively with global teams.Innovates & adapts: Actively generates ideas, encourages experimentation, and promotes learning and improvement within the team.\nRequired SkillsStrong communication and presentation skills.Proficiency in sales techniques and negotiation.Strategic thinking and problem-solving skills.Relationship building, negotia