 the future of digital assets. We're actively building it.\n\nMission statement\nWe are looking for a Head of Engineering / Engineering Lead with strong experience in systematic options trading to lead our Options Engineering team.\n\nIn this role, you will be responsible for leading the Options Engineering team, driving continuous improvement across the trading infrastructure, and supporting the evolution of our systematic options trading platform. This includes areas such as automated quoting, execution, risk controls, pricing workflows, and production reliability.\n\nWe are primarily looking for candidates based in European time zones or the US East Coast time zone.\n\nWe are looking for someone who can:\n\nLead and grow an Options Engineering team of around 7 engineers\n\nBring hands-on experience in systematic options trading, ideally including options market-making, automated quoting, execution, and risk management\n\nOwn and evolve an existing Rust-native systematic options trading platform\n\nProvide strong technical direction across trading infrastructure, system design, performance, reliability, and risk controls\n\nWork pragmatically through complex engineering and trading-system challenges\n\nPartner closely with trading, quant, product, risk, and infrastructure stakeholders\n\nBalance technical leadership with people leadership, delivery ownership, and operational discipline\n\nRequired Experience\n\n7+ years of experience in systematic trading, options market-making or low-latency trading systems\n\nStrong hands-on experience with Rust, C++, or C\n\nWillingness to become deeply proficient in Rust, if not already\n\nStrong understanding of algorithmic options trading, including automated quoting, execution, pricing, risk controls, and market data workflows\n\nExperience building or maintaining low-latency trading systems, ideally within options or derivatives markets\n\nExperience working with SQL databases in production environments, with PostgreSQL pr