ify and prioritize AI opportunities across the platform that deliver measurable customer and business impact.\n\n•Partner with Engineering and Data to shape AI-enabled initiatives into clear product requirements and delivery plans.\n\n• Ensure AI features are measurable and monitored post-launch, with clear success metrics and iteration loops.\n\nAutomation & Operational Scalability:\n\nIdentify high-friction operational workflows and lead automation initiatives that reduce manual effort and cost-to-serve.\n\nPartner with Operations, Finance, Support, and Engineering to map processes, define requirements, and deliver scalable automation.\n\nImprove throughput and reliability through workflow automation, integrations, and systemization of recurring processes.\n\nEstablish measurable targets for operational automation (cycle time, error rate, manual hours saved, SLA compliance) and drive continuous improvement.\n\nExecution & Delivery Leadership:\n\nLead the Delivery team to ensure predictable, high-quality execution across multiple squads.\n\nEstablish delivery standards and rituals: sprint and release planning, execution tracking, risk management, dependency mapping, and escalation paths.\n\nDrive cross-functional coordination across Engineering, Design, Data, and Operations to remove blockers early and keep teams moving.\n\nOwn release readiness and go-live processes, including phased rollouts and post-release retrospectives.\n\nProduct Craft & Decision Quality:\n\nSet the bar for product artifacts and delivery readiness: PRDs, acceptance criteria, rollout strategies, launch plans, and post-launch measurement.\n\nEnsure initiatives are instrumented and measurable, with clear baselines, targets, and monitoring.\n\nRaise the quality of prioritization by grounding decisions in evidence, customer insights, and business impact.\n\nPeople Leadership & Org Building\n\nLead, coach, and develop Product Managers and Delivery leads, including hiring, performance management, and career growth.\n\nBuild a culture of accountability, ownership, and delivery excellence, without sacrificing product quality.\n\nCreate consistency in how teams plan, execute, and communicate progress.\n\nStakeholder & Go-To-Market Leadership:\n\nServe as a senior partner to Marketing, Sales, Partnerships, and Customer teams to shape launches, positioning, and enablement.\n\nCommunicate product direction, progress, risks, and trade-offs with clarity to leadership and cross-functional partners.\n\nWhat Success Looks Like:\n\n• A roadmap that is understood, trusted, and tied to measurable outcomes.\n\n• Delivery becomes predictable: fewer surprises, clearer ownership, faster decision cycles, and healthier execution rhythms.\n\n• AI-enabled initiatives ship with measurable impact and improve through disciplined iteration.\n\n• Operational automation reduces manual effort, improves SLAs, and enables scale without linear headcount growth.\n\n• Core platform and product metrics improve consistently quarter over quarter.\n\nRequired Qualifications:\n\n10 - 12 years of Product Management experience, with 4+ years leading Product Managers and/or delivery functions.\n\nRequired: experience building and scaling high-scale digital platforms, including high traffic environments, large event volumes, and complex cross-team dependencies.\n\nProven track record leading multi-team roadmaps and shipping customer-facing experiences and platform capabilities.\n\nRequired: AI fluency, with experience shipping AI-enabled product capabilities or leading teams delivering them in production environments.\n\nRequired: experience automating business operations to achieve scalability, including workflow automation, systems integrations, and reducing operational cost-to-serve.\n\nStrong product judgment with the ability to turn ambiguity into clear priorities and execution plans.\n\nStrong analytical mindset: metrics design, funnel and cohort thinking, experimentation literacy, and data-driven prioritization.\n\nStrong cross-functional leadership with Engineering and Design, including credibility in technical and UX trade-offs.\n\nExcellent communication and stakeholder management, including executive-ready updates and decision narratives.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nExperience in marketplace or multi-sided platforms.\n\nExperience scaling delivery operations across multiple squads (program management, release management, operational cadences).\n\nFamiliarity with modern experimentation and analytics stacks.\n\nExperience operating in privacy-sensitive environments.\nDepartment\nProduct Management\nLocations\nDubai\nRemote status\nFully Remote"}
