gineering documents and drawings\n* Reduction in engineering rework and non-conformities\n* Effective vendor and client technical coordination\n* Support to fabrication without delays\n* Successful closure of engineering deliverables within project schedules\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nWork Location: Remote"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e844737fa3a8c1ab","title":"Business Development Representative MENA","company":"indaHash","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e844737fa3a8c1ab","description":"About indaHash\n\nindaHash is a global influencer marketing platform connecting brands with over 5 million creators worldwide. We help brands run scalable, data-driven influencer campaigns across multiple markets, working with leading global brands and agencies.\n\nOur mission is simple: make influencer marketing smarter, faster, and more effective.\n\nAbout the role\n\nWe’re looking for a proactive and hungry Business Development Representative to support our growth in the MENA market.\n\nThis role is perfect for someone early in their sales career who enjoys prospecting and hunting, meeting new people, spotting opportunities, and opening doors to new business. You’ll play a key role in building relationships with brands and agencies, identifying opportunities, and helping expand indaHash’s presence in the market.\n\nYou don’t need to have experience in influencer marketing -hunger to be self-motivated to grow the business, experience in advertising, media, digital marketing, or related industries is essential. You will also need to demonstrate previous success in generating new business revenue. What matters most is your drive to generate opportunities and grow business.\n\nWhat you’ll be doing\n\nIdentify and reach out to potential brand and agency partners in the GCC region\nGenerate new business opportunities through outreach, networking, and research\nBuild and maintain a strong pipeline of potential clients\nQualify leads and support the Business Development team in turning opportunities into deals\nCollaborate with internal teams to prepare pitches and proposals\n Track outreach, opportunities, and pipeline activity in CRM tools\nStay up to date with trends in social media, influencer marketing, and the creator economy\n\nWho we’re looking for\n\n1-3 years of experience in sales, lead generation, or business development\nExperience in advertising, media, marketing, or digital industries (essential)\nStrong communication and relationship-building skills\nA proactive mindset and confidence in reaching out to new contacts\nCommercial thinking and interest in the creator economy\nHungry, self-motivated and resilient\nFluent English and Arabic\n\nWhat makes you a great fit\n\nYou have proven experience in generating new business\nYou enjoy building connections and opening conversations\nYou’re curious about brands, campaigns, and how marketing works\nYou’re organised and comfortable managing multiple opportunities\nYou’re motivated by results and growth\n\nWhy indaHash\n\nWork with global brands and international markets\nBe part of the fast-growing creator economy space\nCollaborate with teams across multiple regions\nGrow your career in business development and digital marketing\n Fully remote work environment\n\nindaHash, powered by ArabyAds, is the fastest growing technology platform that connects influencers from all over the world. Currently, indaHash operates in over 88 markets and owns offices in the United Arab Emirates, Singapore, Indonesia, Malaysia, the UK, South Africa and Poland. We cooperate with over 5,000,000 influencers and work with the biggest brands from the Fortune 500.\n\nSince 2016 indaHash has conducted more than 23 000 campaigns for the world’s largest brands (Coca-cola, McDonald’s, L’Oreal, Electrolux and many more) in over 88 markets. indaHash cooperates parallelly with media houses and advertising agencies from around the world to carry out effective global campaigns on Instagram, Facebook, Snapchat, Twitter, TikTok and many more.\noJRCM9krgo"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=eb039f82cf959176","title":"Sales Intern","company":"NITAQ SUPPORTIVE EDUCATION SERVICES L.L.C","location":"{\"city\":\"Sharjah\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Sharjah\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Sharjah\",\"latitude\":25.370878,\"longitude\":55.406593,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"6 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=eb039f82cf959176","description":"Nitaq Academy\n\nNitaq Academy is a career-focused training institute committed to empowering students and professionals through industry-relevant certifications, language courses, digital skills, AI programs, and career development training. We bridge the gap between education and employability by delivering practical, market-driven learning solutions.\n\nPosition Summary\n\nNitaq Academy is looking for a dynamic and motivated *Sales Intern* to support our student admissions and business development activities. The intern will work closely with the sales and counseling team to generate leads, communicate with prospective students, explain course offerings, and assist in converting inquiries into enrollments.\n\nThis internship is ideal for candidates who want practical exposure in *EdTech sales, lead generation, customer handling, and business communication*.\n\nKey Responsibilities1. Lead Generation & Prospecting\n\n* Identify and generate potential student leads through online platforms, referrals, social media, and direct outreach.\n* Build and maintain a pipeline of prospective students and professionals interested in Nitaq Academy courses.\n* Assist in database collection for schools, colleges, corporate clients, and walk-in prospects.\n\n2. Student Counseling & Course Promotion\n\n* Contact inquiries via phone calls, WhatsApp, email, and social media.\n* Explain Nitaq Academy programs, fees, benefits, schedules, and career outcomes.\n* Understand student requirements and recommend suitable courses.\n\n3. Sales Conversion Support\n\n* Follow up regularly with interested leads.\n* Schedule counseling/demo sessions with senior admission advisors.\n* Support the team in achieving weekly and monthly enrollment targets.\n\n4. CRM & Reporting\n\n* Maintain lead records, follow-up status, and sales notes in CRM/Excel sheets.\n* Prepare daily call reports and weekly sales progress updates.\n* Track conversion ratios and customer feedback.\n\n5. Marketing Coordination\n\n* Coordinate with the marketing team regarding campaign-generated leads.\n* Support promotional activities, seminars, webinars, and educational events.\n* Assist in offline student outreach activities when required.\n\n6. Customer Relationship Management\n\n* Build rapport with students and parents.\n* Ensure prompt response to all inquiries.\n* Maintain professional communication to enhance student trust and academy reputation.\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n\n* Currently pursuing or recently completed Bachelor's degree in Business, Marketing, Sales, or related field.\n* Strong verbal communication and convincing skills.\n* Confidence in speaking with students, parents, and working professionals.\n* Basic knowledge of sales process and customer handling.\n* Familiarity with MS Excel, Google Sheets, CRM tools is a plus.\n* Social media communication knowledge is an advantage.\n* English fluency required; Arabic/Hindi/Urdu is a plus.\n\nPreferred Candidate Profile\n\n* Energetic, target-oriented, and eager to learn.\n* Positive attitude with strong interpersonal skills.\n* Interest in Education / EdTech / Training industry.\n* Ability to work in a fast-paced startup environment.\n\nEdTech sales internships in UAE are generally highly target-driven and require lead follow-up, outreach, and conversion support — especially for institutes selling professional courses and certifications.\n\nWhat the Intern Will Gain\n\n* Real-time hands-on experience in Education Sales\n* Professional training in admissions counseling\n* Lead generation and sales funnel management exposure\n* Communication and negotiation skill development\n* Internship certificate + performance-based job opportunity\n\nInternship Benefits\n\n* Monthly Stipend / Incentive Based (As per company policy)\n* Sales performance bonus\n* Completion Certificate\n* Potential full-time employment opportunity based on performance\n\nKPIs / Performance Metrics\n\n* Number of leads generated per week\n* Number of calls/follow-ups completed\n* Demo/counseling appointments scheduled\n* Enrollment conversions achieved\n* CRM update accuracy\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Sharjah (Sharjah)"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ede68b16ec907e1c","title":"Sales Executive – International Business Club","company":"LIM FZE","location":"{\"city\":null,\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"UAE\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"UAE\",\"latitude\":0,\"longitude\":0,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"7 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ede68b16ec907e1c","description":"*About Us:*\nWe are a growing Business Club dedicated to connecting professionals, fostering B2B leads, and providing exclusive networking opportunities. We are looking for a results-driven Sales professional who also has an eye for branding.\n\n*Role Overview: *You will be the sole Sales Executive for the Business Club. Your job is to close memberships via phone and WhatsApp. Because you are speaking with prospects every day, you will also direct the marketing team on what posts and campaigns will actually help sales, and you have final approval authority over all their content and designs before anything goes live.\n\n*Key Responsibilities:*\n\n*1. Sales (Primary Focus):*\n\n* Conduct high-volume outbound calls and WhatsApp messages to prospective business owners and professionals.\n* Pitch the value of our Business Club, overcome objections, and close memberships over the phone.\n* Manage and nurture a pipeline of leads via WhatsApp Business and CRM.\n* Achieve weekly targets for calls, meetings set, and membership sales.\n* Maintain fast response times: reply to prospect inquiries within 15 minutes, and approve/reject marketing content within 2 hours.\n\n*2. Marketing Coordination & Approval:*\n\n* Act as the approval authority for the marketing team before any post or campaign goes live.\n* Review all content (copy) and design (graphics/videos) to ensure alignment with the club's sales message and brand guidelines.\n* Coordinate the content calendar: tell the marketing team what to post based on what you hear from prospects (e.g., \"Prospects keep asking about X benefit—let's make a post about that\").\n\n*Qualifications:*\n\n* Proven experience in inside sales or high-volume cold calling (mandatory).\n* Comfortable using WhatsApp Business for bulk messaging and follow-ups.\n* Strong understanding of social media marketing (Instagram, LinkedIn, Facebook) to know what \"good content\" looks like.\n* Excellent written English for approving captions and scripts.\n* Ability to say \"No\" to bad design/messaging and guide the team to fix it.\n\n*Preferred Skills (not required, but a plus):*\n\n* Experience with CRMs or WhatsApp API tools.\n\n*What We Offer:*\nWe are open to discussing the compensation model during the interview:\n\n* Base salary + commissions, or\n* Full commission basis with uncapped earning potential\n\n*How to Apply:*\nSend an email to *hr@lim.ae* with the following:\n\n* *Subject line:* Sales Executive Application – [Your Name]\n* *Attach your CV* (PDF preferred)\n* *In the email body,* answer this question in 2–3 sentences: _\"A prospect says, 'I'm not interested.' How do you respond?\"_\n\n_Optional:_ Instead of writing, you may include a short voice note (30 seconds max) as an attachment. Voice notes are not required – written answers are perfectly fine.\n\nApplications without the requested answer will not be considered.\n\nWork Location: Remote"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ef65dd80dedb3ace","title":"Horizon Practice Director, META (Remote, UAE)","company":"CrowdStrike","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ef65dd80dedb3ace","description":"As a global leader in cybersecurity, CrowdStrike protects the people, processes and technologies that drive modern organizations. Since 2011, our mission hasn’t changed — we’re here to stop breaches, and we’ve redefined modern security with the world’s most advanced AI-native platform. Our customers span all industries, and they count on CrowdStrike to keep their businesses running, their communities safe and their lives moving forward. We’re also a mission-driven company. We cultivate a culture that gives every CrowdStriker both the flexibility and autonomy to own their careers. We’re always looking to add talented CrowdStrikers to the team who have limitless passion, a relentless focus on innovation and a fanatical commitment to our customers, our community and each other. Ready to join a mission that matters? The future of cybersecurity starts with you.\n\nAbout the Role:\nThe Horizon Practice Director will lead a team of emerging technologies specialist sellers throughout the Middle East, Turkey, and Africa. The Director will lead growth of CrowdStrike’s Cloud, Identity, SIEM, AI security, Threat Intelligence/Managed Hunting, and MDR businesses and drive broader CrowdStrike platform adoption. This function will work with and across CrowdStrike regional sales, sales engineering, marketing, product development, and services organizations to execute Horizon sales playbooks, directly engage customers around CrowdStrike Falcon Platform capabilities, and help customers improve defenses by deploying more of the Horizon Portfolio. This position will be located in the UAE or KSA.\n\nWhat You'll Do:\n\nEstablish partnerships with Regional VPs, Directors, and core sellers to position CrowdStrike's Horizon technologies throughout key META markets\n\nLead Strategic Conversations - build and nurture relationships with key decision-makers, positioning yourself as a trusted advisor to CIOs and CSOs\n\nLead product specialist practice leads in hitting individual product group revenue targets and incorporating their strategies in broader regional strategy.\n\nCollaborate with customers on incorporating Horizon security products within their operational workflows during technical evaluations and post-sales\n\nWork with marketing and sales teams to develop and execute outreach campaigns that develop platform sales pipeline and customer awareness\n\nLead training efforts for internal teams to better position Horizon products\n\nProvide Product Management teams customer feedback pertaining to new and existing features/capabilities\n\nStay well educated and informed about CrowdStrike's vision, product roadmaps, and threat landscape\n\nMay require modified work hours to accommodate accounts in other time zones\n\nTravel up to 50%\n\nWhat You'll Need:\n\nMinimum 8 years' experience in cyber security technology sales\n\nExperience in leading a team of sales professionals\n\nExperience successfully communicating with and advising c-suite, senior management, and analyst/architect-level customers/clients\n\nDemonstrated success selling security at the C-Suite and senior management levels within the marketplace\n\nExperience successfully navigating procurement, contracts, and sales processes\n\nOperational excellence in managing sales pipeline and engagement with internal and external corporate sales teams\n\nExperienced and comfortable presenting to large audiences both virtually and in person\n\nFluency in Arabic\n\nQu